pmc BMC Geriatr BMC Geriatr 33 bmcgeri BMC Geriatrics 1471-2318 BMC PMC12482252 PMC12482252.1 12482252 12482252 41023928 10.1186/s12877-025-06405-7 6405 1 Research A Delphi consensus-based frailty screening scale for community-dwelling older adults in China Wang Qin 1 Zhang Yuhui 1 Li Li 1 Zhao Chongyang 1 Song Jia 1 Zhang Xin 3 Wu Hongmei 4 Kang Deying deyingkang@126.com 1 2 1 https://ror.org/011ashp19 grid.13291.38 0000 0001 0807 1581 Department of Evidence-based Medicine and Clinical Epidemiology, West China Hospital, Sichuan University, 2 https://ror.org/011ashp19 grid.13291.38 0000 0001 0807 1581 Center of Biostatistics, Design, Measurement and Evaluation (CBDME), Department of Clinical Research Management, West China Hospital, Sichuan University, 3 https://ror.org/011ashp19 grid.13291.38 0000 0001 0807 1581 Division of Internal Medicine, Institute of Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine, West China Hospital, Sichuan University, 4 https://ror.org/011ashp19 grid.13291.38 0000 0001 0807 1581 Center for Geriatrics, West China Hospital, Sichuan University, 29 9 2025 2025 25 478199 743 27 5 2025 22 8 2025 29 09 2025 01 10 2025 01 10 2025 © The Author(s) 2025 2025 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/ Open Access http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/ Background Frailty is a multidimensional condition with increasing relevance in aging populations. However, most existing screening tools used in China are either translated from Western instruments or designed for clinical settings, limiting their cultural and practical applicability for community-based screening. This study aims to develop a multifaceted frailty screening scale tailored to the needs of community-dwelling older adults in China. Methods A systematic review and meta-analysis were conducted to identify high-frequency and high-relevance frailty-related items. Based on these findings, a two-round Delphi survey involving 16 experts in geriatrics, public health, and clinical epidemiology was undertaken to refine, evaluate, and finalize the item pool. Results Based on systematic review and Delphi expert consensus, a 22-item screening tool was developed covering physical, psychological, functional, nutritional, medication-related, and social domains. Conclusions The Frailty Screening Scale (FSS) demonstrates good content basis and contextual adaptability as a brief frailty screening tool for community-dwelling older adults in China.It may serve as a complementary tool alongside existing frailty assessment instruments. Supplementary Information The online version contains supplementary material available at 10.1186/s12877-025-06405-7. Keywords Frailty Community-dwelling older adults Screening tool development Delphi method 1.3.5 project for disciplines of excellence-Clinical Research Fund, West China Hospital, Sichuan University 2023HXFH045 Zhang Xin 1.3.5 project for disciplines of excellence, West China Hospital, Sichuan University ZYGD23002 Kang Deying pmc-status-qastatus 0 pmc-status-live yes pmc-status-embargo no pmc-status-released yes pmc-prop-open-access yes pmc-prop-olf no pmc-prop-manuscript no pmc-prop-legally-suppressed no pmc-prop-has-pdf yes pmc-prop-has-supplement yes pmc-prop-pdf-only no pmc-prop-suppress-copyright no pmc-prop-is-real-version no pmc-prop-is-scanned-article no pmc-prop-preprint no pmc-prop-in-epmc yes issue-copyright-statement © BioMed Central Ltd., part of Springer Nature 2025 Introduction Frailty is a multidimensional syndrome linked to increased risks of many adverse outcomes, such as disability, hospitalization, and mortality, posing a growing challenge in aging China [ 1 3 4 5 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
